commit message: Adding an index boundary check to prevent OOB crashes on certain locales
Check that the XMLRPC Fault response is valid, before loading code/message from it.
Try to cast the faultCode to `int` and catch the ClassCastException instead of reading it as string and then parse it to int.
Consume Entity even in case of errors, and improved logging.

Merge pull request #3847 from wordpress-mobile/issue/3846-detaillistpreference-OOB-exception
